utschland (CC BY-NC-SA 3.0 DE)</licence><ab type="version">version-01-22</ab><ab type="edition">Digitale Edition der Korrespondenz August Wilhelm Schlegels</ab><ab type="state">Neu transkribiert und ausgezeichnet; zweimal kollationiert</ab></availability><date when="2022-01-26"/><idno type="url">https://august-wilhelm-schlegel.de/briefedigital/letters/view/4126</idno></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl n="carrier1"><title>Rocher, Rosane und Ludo Rocher: Founders of Western Indology. August Wilhelm von Schlegel and Henry Thomas Colebrooke in correspondence 1820–1837. Wiesbaden 2013, S. 139.</title></bibl><msDesc n="carrier2"><msIdentifier><institution>Dresden, Sächsische Landesbibliothek - Staats- und Universitätsbibliothek</institution><idno type="signatur">Mscr.Dresd.e.90,XIX,Bd.5,Nr.58</idno></msIdentifier><physDesc><objectDesc><ab type="oai">DE-1a-33441</ab><ab type="alternativeOai">DE-1a-1877968</ab><ab type="alternativeSignatur">Mscr.Dresd.e.90,XIX,Bd.5,S.211-212</ab><ab type="type">Manuscript</ab><ab type="subtype">Original</ab><ab type="pages">2S., hs. m. U.</ab><ab type="paper">22,7 x 18,9 cm</ab><ab type="note">Empfangsort erschlossen.</ab></objectDesc></physDesc></msDesc></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><correspDesc ref="https://august-wilhelm-schlegel.de/briefedigital/letters/view/4126"><correspAction type="sent"><persName key="2385" ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/116636688">Henry T. Colebrooke</persName><placeName key="292" ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/4074335-4">London</placeName><date when="1825-06-28">1825-06-28</date></correspAction><correspAction type="received"><persName key="766" ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/118607960">August Wilhelm von Schlegel</persName><placeName key="887" ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/1001909-1">Bonn</placeName></correspAction></correspDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><facsimile><graphic n="1" decls="carrier2" url="https://digital.slub-dresden.de/data/kitodo/AWvS_DE-1a-33441_Bd.5/AWvS_DE-1a-33441_Bd.5_tif/jpegs/00000211.tif.original.jpg"/><graphic n="2" decls="carrier2" url="https://digital.slub-dresden.de/data/kitodo/AWvS_DE-1a-33441_Bd.5/AWvS_DE-1a-33441_Bd.5_tif/jpegs/00000212.tif.original.jpg"/></facsimile><text><body><div><p><hi rend="family:Courier"><milestone unit="start" n="27498"/>[1]</hi><note type="Notiz_zur_Transkription"><title>Paginierung des Editors</title></note><milestone unit="end" n="27498"/><hi rend="family:Courier"> 28</hi><hi rend="family:Courier;offset:4">th</hi><hi rend="family:Courier"> June 1825<lb/>My dear Sir<lb/>I am this moment favord with </hi><ref target="fud://13788"><hi rend="family:Courier">your letter of 19</hi><hi rend="family:Courier;offset:4">th</hi><hi rend="family:Courier"> June</hi></ref><hi rend="family:Courier"> &amp; lose no time (as today is foreign post &amp; near the home) in acknowledging it; defining till </hi><ref target="fud://4128"><hi rend="family:Courier">next post</hi></ref><hi rend="family:Courier"> my answer to most of the subjects of it. I am very much gratified by the very satisfactory account you give of <persName key="8840">my son</persName>. He was always bashful, </hi><hi rend="family:Courier;overstrike:1">and <milestone unit="start" n="46201"/>xxx</hi><note type="Notiz_zur_Transkription"><title>Nicht entzifferte Streichung</title></note><milestone unit="end" n="46201"/><hi rend="family:Courier;overstrike:1"></hi><hi rend="family:Courier"> </hi><hi rend="family:Courier;offset:4">but</hi><hi rend="family:Courier"> I hope will get over his shyness and enjoy the benefit of your kind disposition to communicate instruction to him<lb/>I am very desirous that he should learn to swim; &amp; shall be much obliged by your making arrangements for his being instructed in that very desirable art. </hi><persName key="2565"><hi rend="family:Courier" rendition="#PRSPreset1">Sir</hi><hi rend="family:Courier"> Alexander Johnston</hi></persName><hi rend="family:Courier"> is abroad; at least I have not heard of his return from a little excursion undertaken by him. When he does I will ascertain his wishes as to <persName key="3537">his Sonʼs</persName> learning to swim. I scarcely <milestone unit="start" n="27499"/>[2]</hi><note type="Notiz_zur_Transkription"><title>Paginierung des Editors</title></note><milestone unit="end" n="27499"/><hi rend="family:Courier"> doubt of his wishing it<lb/>On receipt of </hi><ref target="fud://13787"><hi rend="family:Courier">your former letter</hi></ref><hi rend="family:Courier"> I apprised <orgName key="12992">my bankers</orgName> that your next draft would be for 70</hi><hi rend="family:Courier;offset:4;underline:1"><milestone unit="start" n="46200"/>£</hi><note type="Sachkommentar"><title>Pfund Sterling</title></note><milestone unit="end" n="46200"/><hi rend="family:Courier;offset:4;underline:1"></hi><hi rend="family:Courier"> If it should be for something more, pray advise me of it, in time, and I will instruct them accordingly<lb/>I am <lb/>Dear Sir<lb/>very sinc</hi><hi rend="family:Courier;offset:4">ly</hi><hi rend="family:Courier"> Yours<lb/>HColebrooke</hi></p></div></body></text></TEI>
